headline: TXN Q2 Deep Dive: Cyclical Recovery Progresses, but Management Signals Caution Amid Supply Chain Volatility
summary: Analog chip manufacturer Texas Instruments (NASDAQ:TXN) reported Q2 CY2025 results topping the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 16.4% year on year to $4.45 billion. The company expects next quarter’s revenue to be around $4.63 billion, close to analysts’ estimates. Its GAAP profit of $1.41 per share was 5.8% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
